{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim/pullrequests/111/comments/6733640.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/handsim/diff/osrf/handsim:None..None?path=src%2FHaptixWorldPlugin.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/handsim/pull-requests/111/_/diff#comment-6733640"}}, "parent": {"id": 6733343, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim/pullrequests/111/comments/6733343.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/handsim/pull-requests/111/_/diff#comment-6733343"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 111, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim/pullrequests/111.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/handsim/pull-requests/111"}}, "title": "HAPTIX Sim API implementation"}, "content": {"raw": "Another idea: You could replace your `for` loop with two steps:\n\n* `std::remove_if()` with a lambda function where you check if it's time to remove the impulse from `this->wrenchDurations` (the condition of your `if` right now).\n* Apply the force/torque through all the elements of `this->wrenchDurations`.\n\nRef: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erase%E2%80%93remove_idiom", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Another idea: You could replace your <code>for</code> loop with two steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>std::remove_if()</code> with a lambda function where you check if it's time to remove the impulse from <code>this-&gt;wrenchDurations</code> (the condition of your <code>if</code> right now).</li>\n<li>Apply the force/torque through all the elements of <code>this-&gt;wrenchDurations</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ref: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erase%E2%80%93remove_idiom\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erase%E2%80%93remove_idiom</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-05-07T21:48:47.389605+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api